<p><font color="black">
I am currently an Associate Professor with School of Information and Electronics, Beijing Institute of Technology, China. I received the B.S. degree (with the highest honor) in 2009 and Ph.D. degree (with the highest honor) in 2016, both from Beijing Institute of Technology, Beijing, China. Then I worked as a Post-Doc, and later became an Associate Professor in Beijing Institute of Technology. From 2013 to 2015 and from 2018 to 2019, I was a visiting/associate researcher with the Department of Electronic and Electrical Engineering, University of Sheffield, Sheffield, UK.<br />

<br />

I was the recipient of two Excellent Ph.D. Thesis Awards from both the Chinese Institute of Electronics and the Beijing Institute of Technology in 2016. I was also the recipient of Second-Class Prize of the National Award for Technological Invention in 2020, the First-Class Prize of the Science and Technology (Technological Invention) Award from Chinese Institute of Electronics in 2018, and the Second-Class Prize of the Ministerial Level Science and Technology Progress Award in 2014. He serves as the Guest Editor of IJAP. He is the Financial Chair of the IEEE CAPSAP 2021 in Costa Rica, and the Workshop Co-Chair of the CSPS 2020 in Changbaishan, China. He is the regular reviewer for major journals such as IEEE TSP, IEEE WCM, IEEE TAES, IEEE TVT, IEEE SPL, IEEE COMML, Elsevier SP, Elsevier DSP, etc., and the TPC member for international conferences. <br />

<br />

I have more than 12 years of professional experience in system and algorithm design, implementation (through FPGA and DSP), and debugging. I have received three Science and Technology Progress Awards and hold more than 30 patents. <br />

<br />

